ul.li: (Lower) uses SHR (Right-Shift): Bits shifted off the end are permanently destroyed. This introduces non-linearity and prevents the message schedule from being easily reversed.
(Upper) uses only ROTR (Right-Rotate): All 32 bits of information are preserved, just moved to new positions for maximum diffusion.

div.p: CRITICAL BUG WARNING: Naming your compression function sigma0() instead of Sigma0() is the #1 source of silent hash failures. If your hash is wrong, check these constants first!
